<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3365> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3365" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Celebrated as Proconsul a triumph de Liguribus Stoeneis (Act. Tr., Degrassi 84f., 560)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3349> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3349" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Ant., Degrassi 162f. (M. Por[ci.] Cato, Q. [- - - -]); Vell. 1.15.5; 2.7.8; Val. Max. 5.10.3; Plin. NH 2.99; Gell. 13.20.10; Obseq. 35; Eutrop. 4.23.1; Chr. 354 (Catdne et Rige); Fast. Hyd. (Catone et Marcio Rega); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; on Marcius, CIL 1\n     .2.660, but see 68 B.C.; Cic. Cons. fr. 15; and on his filiation, Act. Tr. for 117. See Degrassi 127, 472f. Marcius campaigned against the Stoeni in Liguria (Liv. Per. 62; Oros. 5.14.5). Porcius died in Africa, perhaps while engaged in settling the succession to Micipsa in Numidia (Gell. 13.20.10; cf. Gsell, Hist. anc. Afr. Nord 7.22, 66, 142). At some time in his career he proposed a bill to regulate interest rates (FOR 2.22f., and 118f.). On Cato, see D.- G. 5.161, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3297> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3297" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The latest possible date for their praetorships under the Lex Villia." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10153> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10153" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Liguribus Stoeneis. MRR I.529, Itgenshorst no. 224, Rich no. 224." .
